 <td valign="top" class="vt-content">
 

	
  <div class="vt-datebar">
  <img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: Sat Jan 22, 2011 4:08 pm 
  </div><!-- /vt-datebar --> 
            
       <div class="vt-postcontent">
       that is partly right, except that the sudo -s command will affect only the shell opened with putty and not your scp session, that's why you keep getting that error.<br />You have three options:<br /><br />1. (suggested one) edit the file directly on the Stora as root user, with the already installed &quot;vi&quot; or you can install &quot;nano&quot; through the ipkg package manager;<br />2. edit the file with scp but save it under a different directory (like /home/0common) where your user has write permissions and after, login with ssh, gain root access and move the file from /home/0common back to /etc/init.d<br />3. enable root account direct access (by setting a password with: sudo passwd) so that you can use SCP logging in as root with the set password (be careful with this option, and if you enable it, choose a strong password).
       </div> 
       
       <div id="sig4714" class="signature">--pippone</div>

    
    
 </td><!-- /content -->
